label: cjv
description: coefficient of joint variation (CJV): The cjv of GM and WM was proposed as objective function by [Ganzetti2016] for the optimization of INU correction algorithms. Higher values are related to the presence of heavy head motion and large INU artifacts. Lower values are better

label: cnr
description: contrast-to-noise ratio (CNR): The cnr [Magnota2006], is an extension of the SNR calculation to evaluate how separated the tissue distributions of GM and WM are. Higher values indicate better quality

label: efc
description: The EFC [Atkinson1997] uses the Shannon entropy of voxel intensities as an indication of ghosting and blurring induced by head motion. Lower values are better

label: fber
description: The FBER [Shehzad2015], defined as the mean energy of image values within the head relative to outside the head [QAP-measures]. Higher values are better.

label: fwhm_avg
description: The FWHM of the spatial distribution of the image intensity values in units of voxels [Forman1995]. Lower values are better, higher values indicate a blurrier image. Average of the x, y and z dimensions

label: fwhm_x
description: The FWHM of the spatial distribution of the image intensity values in units of voxels [Forman1995]. Lower values are better, higher values indicate a blurrier image. Measured in the x dimension

label: fwhm_y
description: The FWHM of the spatial distribution of the image intensity values in units of voxels [Forman1995]. Lower values are better, higher values indicate a blurrier image.Measured in the y dimension

label: fwhm_z
description: The FWHM of the spatial distribution of the image intensity values in units of voxels [Forman1995]. Lower values are better, higher values indicate a blurrier image. Measured in the z dimension

label: icvs_csf
description: the ICV fractions of CSF. It should move within a normative range.

label: icvs_gm
description: the ICV fractions of GM. It should move within a normative range.

label: icvs_wm
description: the ICV fractions of WM. It should move within a normative range.

label: inu_med
description: summary statistic (median) of the INU field (bias field) as extracted by the N4ITK algorithm [Tustison2010]. Values closer to 1.0 are better, values further from zero indicate greater RF field inhomogeneity.

label: inu_range
description: summary statistic (range) of the INU field (bias field) as extracted by the N4ITK algorithm [Tustison2010]. Values closer to 1.0 are better, values further from zero indicate greater RF field inhomogeneity.

label: rpve_csf
description: the rPVe of CSF. Lower values are better.

label: rpve_gm
description: the rPVe of GM. Lower values are better.

label: rpve_wm
description: the rPVe of WM. Lower values are better.

label: snr_csf
description: signal-to-noise ratio (SNR): calculated within the CSF.

label: snr_gm
description: signal-to-noise ratio (SNR): calculated within the GM.

label: snr_total
description: signal-to-noise ratio (SNR): calculated within the total brain.

label: snr_wm
description: signal-to-noise ratio (SNR): calculated within the WM.

label: snrd_csf
description: Dietrich’s SNR (SNRd) as proposed by [Dietrich2007], using the air background as reference. Calculated within the CSF.

label: snrd_gm
description: Dietrich’s SNR (SNRd) as proposed by [Dietrich2007], using the air background as reference. Calculated within the GM.

label: snrd_total
description: Dietrich’s SNR (SNRd) as proposed by [Dietrich2007], using the air background as reference. Calculated within the total brain.

label: snrd_wm
description: Dietrich’s SNR (SNRd) as proposed by [Dietrich2007], using the air background as reference. Calculated within the WM.

label: summary_bg_k
description: Kurtosis of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_mad
description: Median absolute deviation (mad) of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_mean
description: Mean of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_median
description: Median of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_n
description: Number of voxels of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_p05
description: 5% percentile of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_p95
description: 95% percentile of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_bg_stdv
description: Standard deviation of the distribution of background (bg).

label: summary_csf_k
description: Kurtosis of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_mad
description: Median absolute deviation (mad) of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_mean
description: Mean of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_median
description: Median of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_n
description: Number of voxels of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_p05
description: 5% percentile of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_p95
description: 95% percentile of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_csf_stdv
description: Standard deviation of the distribution of CSF.

label: summary_gm_k
description: Kurtosis of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_mad
description: Median absolute deviation (mad) of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_mean
description: Mean of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_median
description: Median of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_n
description: Number of voxels of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_p05
description: 5% percentile of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_p95
description: 95% percentile of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_gm_stdv
description: Standard deviation of the distribution of GM.

label: summary_wm_k
description: Kurtosis of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_mad
description: Median absolute deviation (mad) of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_mean
description: Mean of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_median
description: Median of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_n
description: Number of voxels of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_p05
description: 5% percentile of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_p95
description: 95% percentile of the distribution of WM.

label: summary_wm_stdv
description: Standard deviation of the distribution of CSF.

label: tpm_overlap_csf
description: The overlap of the TPMs estimated from the image and the corresponding maps from the ICBM nonlinear-asymmetric 2009c template for the CSF. Higher values are better.

label: tpm_overlap_gm
description: The overlap of the TPMs estimated from the image and the corresponding maps from the ICBM nonlinear-asymmetric 2009c template for the GM. Higher values are better.

label: tpm_overlap_wm
description: The overlap of the TPMs estimated from the image and the corresponding maps from the ICBM nonlinear-asymmetric 2009c template for the WM. Higher values are better.

label: wm2max
description: The white-matter to maximum intensity ratio is the median intensity within the WM mask over the 95% percentile of the full intensity distribution, that captures the existence of long tails due to hyper-intensity of the carotid vessels and fat. Values should be around the interval [0.6, 0.8].
